    "safe_for_commercial_reuse": true,
    "attribution": "Items drawn from the International Personality Item Pool (Goldberg, L. R., 1999; https://ipip.ori.org). Scale developed and validated by DeYoung, C. G., Quilty, L. C., & Peterson, J. B. (2007). Between facets and domains: 10 aspects of the Big Five. Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 93(5), 880-896. Verbatim item text and keying obtained from the official IPIP scoring-key page (https://ipip.ori.org/BFASKeys.htm). The BFI-derived item is credited to John, O. P., Naumann, L. P., & Soto, C. J. (2008).",
    "scoring_notes": "10 aspect scales, 10 items each. Big Five domains = mean of their two aspect scales (20 items each): Neuroticism = Volatility + Withdrawal; Agreeableness = Compassion + Politeness; Conscientiousness = Industriousness + Orderliness; Extraversion = Enthusiasm + Assertiveness; Openness/Intellect = Intellect + Openness. Response scale: 5-point (1 = Very Inaccurate to 5 = Very Accurate). Items marked keyed \"-\" are reverse-scored. Published aspect alphas (n from original sample): Volatility .85, Withdrawal .84, Compassion .84, Politeness .75, Industriousness .81, Orderliness .80, Enthusiasm .81, Assertiveness .85, Intellect .84, Openness .78.",
    "cautions": "All 100 items were fetched verbatim from the official IPIP scoring-key page (https://ipip.ori.org/BFASKeys.htm) and independently re-verified against the raw page HTML via curl — the two sources matched exactly. Structure confirmed: 10 aspect scales x 10 items = 100 items, 20 items per Big Five domain (2 aspects each). Numbering here (1-100) reflects the order on the IPIP page (Volatility, Withdrawal, Compassion, Politeness, Industriousness, Orderliness, Enthusiasm, Assertiveness, Intellect, Openness), positively-keyed items first then negatively-keyed within each aspect; it is NOT the randomized administration order used in the original study. LICENSE NUANCE: the task framed all items as public-domain IPIP, which is true for 98/100. Two items are exceptions and should be flagged before any redistribution: \"Am not a very enthusiastic person.\" (Enthusiasm, newly written for the BFAS, not from IPIP) and \"Do not have an assertive personality.\" (Assertiveness, a reverse-wording of a copyrighted BFI item). Both remain safe for non-commercial research use. Response format is not part of item text: the standard IPIP/BFAS administration prepends the stem \"I\" and uses a 5-point Likert scale (1 = Very Inaccurate ... 5 = Very Accurate); reverse-key the \"-\" items before scoring. Since this corpus is a stage-1 collection that will be rewritten into plain language, retain the factor/facet/keyed metadata so scoring survives the rewrite. The 2007 article appendix lists these same items and is the authoritative print source.",
